# Delta Learn Backend

Django 6 + DRF + SQLite backend for the Delta Learn platform.

## Architecture

```
Delta-Learn-Backend/
├── delta_learn/          # Django project (settings, urls, wsgi)
├── chapters/             # Core app: Subject, Chapter, Question, Takeaway, Highlight, Note
├── users/                # Auth app: register, login (JWT), /me
├── fixtures/             # JSON seed data exported from the original React app
└── manage.py
```

## Models (chapters app)

| Model     | Key fields                                                                 |
|-----------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Subject   | slug (unique), name, description, accent_color, order                     |
| Chapter   | subject FK, chapter_number, part, title, subtitle, order                  |
| Question  | chapter FK, order, question, difficulty, tldr, answer, points (JSON), diagram, diagram2, table_data (JSON), followup |
| Takeaway  | chapter FK, order, content (HTML)                                         |
| Highlight | user FK, chapter FK, question_index, text, color (yellow/green/blue/pink) |
| Note      | user FK, subject FK (nullable), chapter FK (nullable), content, ai_summary |

## API Endpoints

### Public (no auth)
- `GET /api/subjects/` — list all subjects with chapter_count and written_count
- `GET /api/subjects/{slug}/` — subject detail with ordered chapter list
- `GET /api/subjects/{slug}/chapters/{number}/` — full chapter with nested questions + takeaways

### Auth (`/api/auth/`)
- `POST /api/auth/register/` — create account (username, email, password)
- `POST /api/auth/login/` — returns JWT access + refresh tokens
- `POST /api/auth/token/refresh/` — refresh access token
- `GET /api/auth/me/` — current user profile (requires Bearer token)

### Authenticated (`/api/`)
- `GET/POST /api/highlights/` — list (filterable by ?subject=&chapter=) / create
- `DELETE /api/highlights/{id}/` — remove highlight
- `GET/POST /api/notes/` — list (filterable by ?subject=&chapter=) / create
- `GET/PATCH/DELETE /api/notes/{id}/` — read/update/delete note
- `POST /api/notes/{id}/analyze/` — AI analysis placeholder

## Conventions

### Adding a new model
1. Define in `chapters/models.py` with proper `Meta.ordering` and `__str__`
2. Register in `chapters/admin.py` with list_display, list_filter, search_fields
3. Create serializer in `chapters/serializers.py` — use camelCase field aliases for frontend compatibility
4. Add view in `chapters/views.py` and route in `chapters/urls.py`
5. Run `python manage.py makemigrations && python manage.py migrate`

### Serializer naming
- Use camelCase for JSON keys consumed by the frontend (e.g., `accentColor`, `diagramCaption`, `_dbId`)
- Map to snake_case model fields via `source=` parameter

### Authentication
- JWT via djangorestframework-simplejwt
- Access token: 1 hour lifetime; refresh token: 14 days
- Public endpoints use `permission_classes = [AllowAny]`
- Authenticated endpoints use `permission_classes = [IsAuthenticated]`
- User-scoped querysets: always filter by `user=self.request.user`

### Seed data
- JSON fixtures live in `fixtures/` (system-design.json, dsa.json, ai.json)
- `python manage.py seed_data` loads them; `--clear` wipes first
- When adding new chapter content, update the fixture JSON or use Django Admin

### CORS
- Allowed origins defined in `settings.py`: localhost:5173, delta-learn.netlify.app
- Add new frontend domains to `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS`

